<h1>Randonnae</h1>

<p><b>Randonnae</b> is a web application written in
Ruby-On-Rails, that aims to provide a nice and easy way to store pictures taken
during a trek, and to display them with the according GPS trace on a slippy
map.</p>

<% if current_user %>

  <p>Hey <%=current_user.name %> ! Why not dropping a zip file containing a GPX and your photos ?</p>

<%else %>

  <p> In order to be able to use the application, you will need to <%= link_to "authenticate
   using Oauth and your OpenStreetMap account", "/auth/osm" %></p>

<% end %>

